# RDS overview

Runs the engine on **EC2 + EBS** behind the scenes; you get a **connection endpoint**, a **maintenance window**, and config knobs.

## AWS owns / you own

- **AWS:** OS, engine, patching, hardware, backups, replicas, Multi-AZ failover
- **You:** schema, queries, data
- Trade: **no SSH / no OS access** → uncertified features out of reach

## Six engines

**MySQL · PostgreSQL · MariaDB · Oracle · SQL Server · IBM Db2**

All share the managed plane: automated backups, Multi-AZ, read replicas, Performance Insights, parameter/option groups (matrix varies per engine).

**Default relational tier** unless you need OS control or an uncertified feature.
